olive oil
1 carrot
1 tomato
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Seasoning Blend
½ packet yellow curry paste
1 packet tomato paste
1 box coconut milk
2 tsp soy sauce
½ cup water
1 packet Daikon Noodles
1 bunch Asian Greens
3 clove garlic

• Cut carrot into half-moons. Cut tomato into
bite-sized chunks. Roughly chop Asian greens.
Finely chop garlic.

• In a medium bowl, combine beef mince,
seasoning blend and 1/2 the garlic. Season with
pepper.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of
the beef mixture into small meatballs (4-5 per
person). Transfer to a plate.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive
oil over medium-high heat. Cook meatballs,
turning, until browned, 4-5 minutes (cook in
batches if your pan is getting crowded). Transfer
to a plate.

TIP: The meatballs will finish cooking in the curry.

• SPICY! You may find the curry paste hot! Add less
if you're sensitive to heat.
• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with
a drizzle of olive oil. Cook carrot and tomato
until tender, 3-4 minutes.
• Add yellow curry paste (see ingredients),
tomato paste, meatballs and the remaining
garlic and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.

• Reduce heat to medium, then add coconut
milk, the soy sauce and water and cook until
reduced and meatballs have cooked through,
2-3 minutes.
• Add daikon noodles and stir to combine.
• Add Asian greens and cook until slightly wilted,
2-3 minutes.

TIP: Add a splash more water if the sauce looks
too thick.

• Divide beef meatball and daikon noodle curry
between bowls. Enjoy!